# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLIENT-SIDE build variables (safe to expose — they ship in the JS bundle).
# Copy to .env for local development.
#
# ⚠️  NEVER put server secrets here. Anything prefixed VITE_ is embedded
#     into the public client bundle at build time.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID="your-project-id"
VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://your-project-id.supabase.co"
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="your-anon-publishable-key"
VITE_AZURE_SPEECH_REGION="southeastasia"
VITE_AZURE_ENDPOINT="https://your-speech-resource.cognitiveservices.azure.com/"

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SERVER-SIDE secrets — these do NOT belong in this file or in any file
# committed to git. Set them as Supabase Edge Function secrets instead:
#
#   supabase secrets set GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS="$(cat GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS.json)"
#   supabase secrets set CUSTOMIMAGE="$(cat customimage.json)"
#   supabase secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
#
# or via Dashboard → Project Settings → Edge Functions → Secrets.
# See docs/SECRETS_SETUP.md for the full guide.
#
#   GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS  → raw JSON of the Cloud Vision service account
#   CUSTOMIMAGE         → raw JSON of the Custom Search credentials
#   GOOGLE_CSE_ID       → Custom Search Engine ID (cx)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
